{
  "texts": [
    "These findings highlight the transformative potential of metric learning for enhancing data-driven, expert-in-the-loop automation in microfossil identification, marking a significant advancement in the automatic analysis and classification of micropaleontological data.",
    "Mitra et al. (2019) utilize VGG16 and ResNet50 networks to classify six species critical for paleoceanographic research.",
    "This study demonstrates that model performance, using digital images captured under varied illumination angles, surpasses both expert and novice human classifiers in terms of precision and recall.",
    "The research lays the groundwork for FORABOT, a robotic system designed to streamline the identification of Foraminifera for geochemical analysis and census counts.",
    "Balancing the system's impressive accuracy is the fact that it is restricted to a select group of species, raising concerns about model bias and suggesting its broader applicability to the full spectrum of extant planktonic Foraminifera will be challenging."
  ]
}